                    <history>
                        <origin notBefore="1250" notAfter="1299" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">
                            <p>Written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace> in <origDate
                                    notBefore="1250" notAfter="1299">the second half of the
                                    thirteenth century</origDate> (see e.g. <bibl>
                                    <ref type="secondary-1" target="IHFol2">Hreinn Benediktsson
                                        1965</ref>
                                    <biblScope unit="pages">xliv</biblScope>
                                </bibl>). Kålund's dating: The thirteenth century.</p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>According to the AM-slip concerning <title>Pétrs saga postola</title>
                                this part of the manuscript belonged to <name type="person"
                                    key="ThoSig004">Þorsteinn Sigurðsson</name>. He once got it from
                                    <name type="place">Northern Iceland</name>, but not from <name
                                    type="place">Austfjörður</name>. The history of <title>Páls saga
                                    postola</title> is unknown.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <acquisition>
                            <p>From the AM-slip, telling only the story of <title type="uniform"
                                    >Pétrs saga postola</title>, it can be infered that <name
                                    type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> acquired the
                                two sagas seperately. He got <title type="uniform">Pétrs saga
                                    postola</title> from <name type="person" key="ThoSig004"
                                    >Þorsteinn Sigurðsson</name> in <date when="1716">1716</date>.
                                The acquisition of <title type="uniform">Páls saga postola</title>
                                is unknown.</p>
                        </acquisition>
